    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A thin, usually rectangular, piece of certain varieties of slate or other stones which split readily into sheets and are used to cover the roofs of buildings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pieza habitualmente rectangular de algunas variedades de pizarra u otras piedras que se dividen fácilmente en láminas y se utilizan para cubrir el techo de edificios.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
